## Architecture
Single-agent (Hermes) with delegate_task for heavy subtasks.
No sub-agent spawn — all routing through delegation.

## Routing Protocol

### Command Triggers
| Command | Action |
|---------|--------|
| `[SAVE]` | Extract key insight → write to memory/{date}.md |
| `[SEARCH:ARCHIVE]` | session_search for past conversations |
| `[SEARCH:WIKI]` | Search wiki/ directory for reference material |
| `[TLDR]` | Executive summary of current context |
| `[PLAN]` | Create structured action plan with priorities |
| `[REVIEW]` | End-of-day review and open loop check |
| `[FORGE:BUILD]` | Full implementation — delegate_task for coding |
| `[FORGE:UPGRADE]` | Modify existing code — delegate_task |
| `[FORGE:QA]` | Quality check — delegate_task |

### Implicit Routing
- 코딩 요청 → delegate_task with coding context
- 리서치 요청 → browser tool for research, write summary
- 스케줄 관련 → check calendar signals, suggest actions
- 감정/에너지 낮음 감지 → switch to supportive mode

## Memory Protocol

### Write Rules
- Use Hermes memory tool for persistent cross-session facts
- Daily logs: write to memory/{YYYY-MM-DD}.md via terminal
- MEMORY.md: promoted insights only (weekly distillation)
- Before writing: read existing to avoid duplicates

### Read Rules
- Session start: read MEMORY.md + latest memory/{date}.md
- On topic reference: session_search for prior context
- On wiki reference: read from wiki/ directory

### Promotion Criteria
- Fact referenced 3+ times → promote to MEMORY.md
- Decision with ongoing impact → promote immediately
- Preference/style discovery → promote to USER-PROFILE section

